additional_house_rules: This is my cosy little apartment in the upper east side, I love it here and I hope you will too! Please treat it as you would treat your own home, i.e. No parties, no shoes on the sofa, no smoking.
description:
My home is cosy and accommodating, great transport links right next to the Q train on 86th street. Some lovely places to eat and drink on the doorstep, laundry and amenities very close by and on the ground floor, so no walk ups!

Location, space, peace and quiet from the noise of the bustling city on your doorstep.
10 minute walk from Central Park and the Met museum, great transport links, some charming local bars and brunch spots

Very easy public transport, the subway Q train is right by the apartment on 2nd Ave at the end of my street. The 4,5,6 are very close at 86th and Lex also.

hosts.about:
I'm a Scottish girl living in New York. I work in the finance sector. In my spare time, I'm a bit of a musician.

For all my guests I try to be as welcoming and accommodating as possible, I have traveled fairly extensively and I know that the little things mean a lot, so if there's anything you need to help you enjoy your stay just let me know.
